      <abstract>
        <p>35 year old with ruptured lateral wall of Left ventricle (LV) resulting in large pseudo aneurysm contained within the pericardium [<xref ref-type="fig" rid="F1">Figure 1</xref>]. There was free flow of blood between the LV and pseudoaneurysm.He underwent endoventricular patch plasty of the defect after opening the wall of aneurysm [<xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">Figure 2</xref>].</p>
